## Quick Reference

### Adding a New Terminal Command

1. Create app class in `assets/js/terminal/apps/command-name.js`:
```javascript
class CommandNameApp {
    constructor(terminal, filesystem, windowManager, os) {
        this.terminal = terminal;
        this.filesystem = filesystem;
        this.windowManager = windowManager;
        this.os = os;
    }

    async run(args) {
        // Implementation
    }
}

window.CommandNameApp = CommandNameApp;
```

2. Register in `assets/js/terminal/core.js`:
   - Add to `handleCommand()` switch statement
   - Add to `runCommand()` appMap
   - Add to tab completion list

### Adding New Data

1. Update YAML/JSON in `_data/` directory
2. Access via `window.JEKYLL_DATA` in JavaScript
3. Update `filesystem-loader.js` if filesystem structure changes

### Styling Guidelines

- Use CSS variables for theming
